  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nA user on Discord reports a panic when UPnP is enabled:\r\n\r\n```\r\nlighthousebeacon  | thread 'tokio-runtime-worker' panicked at 'invalid url or method: Error(InvalidBaseUrl)', /cargo/registry/src/index.crates.io-6f17d22bba15001f/attohttpc-0.16.3/src/request/builder.rs:52:41\r\nlighthousebeacon  | stack backtrace:\r\nlighthousebeacon  |    0: rust_begin_unwind\r\nlighthousebeacon  |              at ./rustc/d5c2e9c342b358556da91d61ed4133f6f50fc0c3/library/std/src/panicking.rs:593:5\r\nlighthousebeacon  |    1: core::panicking::panic_fmt\r\nlighthousebeacon  |              at ./rustc/d5c2e9c342b358556da91d61ed4133f6f50fc0c3/library/core/src/panicking.rs:67:14\r\nlighthousebeacon  |    2: core::result::unwrap_failed\r\nlighthousebeacon  |              at ./rustc/d5c2e9c342b358556da91d61ed4133f6f50fc0c3/library/core/src/result.rs:1651:5\r\nlighthousebeacon  |    3: igd::gateway::Gateway::perform_request\r\nlighthousebeacon  |    4: igd::gateway::Gateway::get_external_ip\r\nlighthousebeacon  |    5: tokio::runtime::task::raw::poll\r\nlighthousebeacon  | note: Some details are omitted, run with `RUST_BACKTRACE=full` for a verbose backtrace.\r\nlighthousebeacon  | Dec 19 16:32:28.108 CRIT Task panic. This is a bug!              advice: Please check above for a backtrace and notify the developers, message: <none>, task_name: UPnP\r\nlighthousebeacon  | Dec 19 16:32:28.108 INFO Internal shutdown received              reason: Panic (fatal error)\r\nlighthousebeacon  | Dec 19 16:32:28.108 INFO Shutting down..                         reason: Failure(\"Panic (fatal error)\")\r\nlighthousebeacon  | Dec 19 16:32:28.109 INFO Saved DHT state                         service: network\r\nlighthousebeacon  | Dec 19 16:32:28.109 INFO Network service shutdown                service: network\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Steps to resolve\r\n\r\nProbably requires patching `igd` to make it less panicky (again).\r\n\r\n## Version\r\n\r\nLighthouse v4.5.0\r\n\r\n## Additional Info\r\n\r\nSimilar to #4171 which was fixed in v4.2.0 (see https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/commit/edbb47dd038d1dcfb86f957852a70c7e885270e4).",
